{
  "stem": "12402.1",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[INAUDIBLE] He was-- was the younger brother, followed Hymie.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They were together.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And right after that, in-- in 1937-- oh, no, 1935, my next brother-- there were three of them-- the third brother left for Israel.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They didn't want to stay in the whole small town, not because they didn't have what to eat or they-- they were short of anything, but they wanted to travel.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They wanted to get away from-- from Poland.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So he ended up in Tel Aviv, you know.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they struggled in those years.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It was very hard times in Israel.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We used to send him parcels and all kind of things.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And in a year, a few years later, in 1937, my older sister, Ray, she left to Montreal to-- to join-- to marry one of my brother's friends, Nathan Heisler.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And she got married in '37 when she got to Montreal.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] after that, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] in '39, in 1939, just before the war, so my older brother came for a visit home.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "It was a great joy to have him there.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "You know, it was very exciting.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And unfortunately, he had to leave just before the war to run away from the-- there were rumors the-- the war is going-- is going to come very quickly, and so he left.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "He went.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "He managed to get back to-- to New York.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "He got the last boat went out-- out of Paris.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "At that time, as a matter of fact, they sank-- the German-- the war got on and they sank a boat.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "We thought for sure he was on the boat.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Well, anyway, that's not the story.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "But and then I went back to yeshiva, in 19-- [INAUDIBLE] 1930-- after Pesach, it was still '34.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
